    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix NULL pointer dereference in VNF UL node sync handling\n\n### Summary\nThe VNF P7 message handlers for UL node synchronization were dereferencing a NULL pointer when processing messages from unregistered PHY instances. This occurred because the code did not validate the return value of `vnf_p7_connection_info_list_find()` before accessing the connection structure.\n\nThis fix adds proper NULL checks after calling `vnf_p7_connection_info_list_find()` in both the LTE and NR versions of the UL node sync handlers. When a connection is not found for the given PHY ID, the functions now log an appropriate error message and return gracefully instead of crashing.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/vnf/src/vnf_p7.c`: Added NULL pointer checks in `vnf_handle_ul_node_sync()` and `vnf_nr_handle_ul_node_sync()` functions.\n- Added error logging when PHY connection lookup fails.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Start the VNF with P7 interface enabled\n2. Send an UL_NODE_SYNC message with a PHY ID that is not registered with the VNF\n3. The VNF will crash with a segmentation fault when trying to access the NULL connection pointer\n\nAfter applying this fix, the VNF will log an error message and continue processing other messages normally.\n"
}